      "activity_preamble": "In this capstone activity, you will evaluate strategies households can use to manage the effects of inflation on their finances. Using the Maya household scenario and a neutral strategy menu, you will apply explicit criteria and trade-offs to defend a justified choice.",
      "learner_task": "### Your tasks:\n1. Read the orientation and framing materials setting the decision context.\n2. Construct perspectives on who gains and loses under different strategies.\n3. Study the criteria exposition presenting ≥3 operational dimensions for evaluation.\n4. Review the worked judgement modelling note contrasting weak versus strong strategy evaluations.\n5. Engage in guided inquiry and guided judgement using the provided comparison table with partial exemplar rows.\n6. Complete an independent judgement memo using the scaffolded template/task cards.\n7. Verify your evaluation using the detailed checklist rubric.\n8. Reflect on your evaluative judgement process.\n9. Transfer your evaluation skills by applying criteria to your own or a hypothetical household strategy with a detailed transfer prompt.\n10. Conclude with a consolidation summary capturing key insights and lessons learned.",
